<TITLE>Drinks company ready for first round of interviews for 20 000 gin tasting job</TITLE>
<TEXT>
A company advertising for a gintern has cherry picked its favourite applicants from more than 5 000 hopefuls who will now have to prove their drinking abilities The dream job will see one lucky person travelling the world sampling different versions of the delicious drink while being paid 20 000 a year And so unsurprisingly when the advert was first posted it generated plenty of interest so much so that the company behind it ILoveGin had to delay their recruitment process However now it is time to move onto the next stage which will see ILoveGin contact the best applicants to ask them to review a recent gin or mixer As the process continues future rounds of ginterviews will include visiting distilleries and plenty of taste testing Toby Vacher who founded ILoveGin com said We knew people would love the Ginternship but we never expected more than a few hundred to make the effort to apply We ve been blown away by the interest and even seen news channels in Europe and the USA pick up the story One of them ran a feature preceded by Snoop Dogg singing about Gin n Juice The world has gone gin crazy and we re hoping to help more and more people discover their new favourite G T Whoever eventually gets the job will work one day a month in London but the rest of the time they can set their own hours and travel to discover new drinks The two day a week internship will run for six months and may lead to a full time position The job spec says you d typically be visiting 1 2 new gin companies each week and apart from the day in London you ll be able to work remotely from home a coffee shop or wherever you wish You might also be interested in 
